summary:
The Council:

1. Decides to renew UNMIN's mandate until 23 January 2009, taking into account the completion of some elements and ongoing work on arms management.

2. Calls upon all parties to utilize UNMIN's expertise to support the peace process.

3. Expects the current monitoring arrangements to conclude within the period of this mandate.
The Security Council:

Endorses the Secretary-General's recommendations for a phased and gradual drawdown and withdrawal of UNMIN staff, including arms monitors; 

Requests the Secretary-General to keep the Council informed of progress, and submit a report on implementation and implications for UNMIN by 31 October 2008; 

Calls on the Nepalese Government to create conditions for UNMIN's withdrawal by the end of its current mandate, including implementing the 25 June Agreement; 

Urges all parties in Nepal to cooperate to continue the transition to a durable solution for a peaceful, democratic and prosperous future; 

Requests parties to ensure the safety, security and freedom of movement of UNMIN and associated personnel; 

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
